{
  "texts": [
    "On this conception, the spatial boundaries of objects are determined by the space occupied by these parts.",
    "A perennial problem with this way of thinking is that determining parthood, and so spatial boundaries, is difficult.",
    "Is a hair (and the fundamental parts that make it up) a part of someone's body?",
    "Does it continue to be so only while it is rooted in the follicle or also when it has been 'shed' but not detached?",
    "Different answers to questions like these give us different mereological sums, and we might wonder which of these is really the person's body."
  ]
}